  "title": "HClO4 and KClO4 buffer - chlorite ion structure",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR078373.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Consider the Lewis electron-dot diagram for the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O 2 with a negative 1 charge\"><math alttext=\"C l O 2 with a negative 1 charge\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>ClO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ion that minimizes formal charge. Which of the following is true about the hybridization of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l\"><math alttext=\"C l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atom in the ion?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l\"><math alttext=\"C l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atom is not hybridized, and the ion contains one single <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O\"><math alttext=\"C l O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext><mo>−</mo><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> bond and one double <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O\"><math alttext=\"C l O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext><mo>−</mo><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> bond.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l\"><math alttext=\"C l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atom is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s p\"><math alttext=\"s p\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> hybridized, and the ion contains two equivalent <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O\"><math alttext=\"C l O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext><mo>−</mo><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> double bonds.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l\"><math alttext=\"C l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atom is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s p 2\"><math alttext=\"s p 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> hybridized, and the ion contains two equivalent <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O\"><math alttext=\"C l O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext><mo>−</mo><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> single bonds.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l\"><math alttext=\"C l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> atom is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s p 3\"><math alttext=\"s p 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> hybridized, and the ion contains two equivalent <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l O\"><math alttext=\"C l O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Cl</mtext><mo>−</mo><mtext>O</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> single bonds.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
